      "id" : "meta::pure::functions::relation::_range_Number_1__Number_1___Range_1_",
      "documentation" : "Returns a window frame, which defines a logically computed set of rows specified by starting and ending points. When the ORDER BY expression is ascending (ASC), the syntax n FOLLOWING means rows with values greater than (or later than) x, and n PRECEDING means rows with values less than (or earlier than) x, where x is the ORDER BY value for the current row. When the ORDER BY expression is descending (DESC), the opposite is true. The offsets 0 PRECEDING and 0 FOLLOWING are equivalent to CURRENT ROW.",
